Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.10,0:00:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We shall resume.\NThe question is if there is no personal self,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.47,0:00:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,how do phenomena come about?\NWell, they come about spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.55,0:00:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,through the process not of evolution or causation\Nbut through emergence
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.75,0:00:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,which the science has recently caught up with.\NBut the because of the evolutionary nature of the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.90,0:00:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,universe and of human uh life potentiality becomes\Nactuality when local conditions are favorable.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.86,0:00:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah,\Nit comes about and of course we'll have a slide just
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.30,0:01:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,quickly reviewing advanced theoretical physics\Nwhich you're all dying to know about.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.42,0:01:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Mindful universe just came out Henry Stap it was\Navailable off the internet now it's available as a book
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.58,0:01:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and the price has come down\Nand it's quite reasonable now uh for those
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.36,0:01:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that really want to understand better the mathematics.\NYeah, potentiality emerges then.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.73,0:01:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So the idea of a personal self is the big barrier to\Nenlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.74,0:01:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The presumption\Nthat there is a personal self making all decisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.51,0:01:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh and that this arm just went that way\Nbecause I decided it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.14,0:01:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't decide it.\NI didn't even think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.79,0:01:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It happened of its own.\NBut see, it does it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.59,0:01:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's stop that.\NPut this thing away.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.91,0:01:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NIt goes out and waves like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.73,0:02:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't watch it, I say, you see what it does?\NIt does it by itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.43,0:02:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,One day you'll c you'll catch it.\NYou'll catch that the phenomena are occurring independent
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.56,0:02:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,of any personal decision.\NThere isn't any personal you uh making decisions
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.41,0:02:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh etc.\NThere is no personal self.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.27,0:02:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So long as you believe\Nthat there's a personal self making these decisions,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.75,0:02:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you will then have to take karmic responsibility for them,\Nyou'll be at the subject of karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.86,0:02:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Buddha warned against it.\NThe Buddha warned against it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.34,0:02:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You see if you uh choose hum humanness then you have to\Ntake the karma that goes within goes with humanness
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.39,0:03:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and so the Buddha war you know recommended to avoid\Nreincarnating because you will reincarnate into the world
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.01,0:03:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,of suffering sickness old age\Nand death poverty sickness suffering old age and death.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.33,0:03:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha sounds a little bit like a pessimist, right?\NHe never won met anybody that won the lottery
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.15,0:03:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,or met a lovely woman and got to marry her\Nand everything like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.83,0:03:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddhist sort of had a stringent view of human life.\NWell,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.00,0:03:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,it's because he was naive\Nand protected from the realities of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.11,0:03:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he got away from his parents somehow\Nand wandered into town and he saw old people sickness,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.11,0:03:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,poverty, and death.\NAnd he never got over the trauma of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.42,0:03:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,He needed psychotherapy.\NOld age sickness, poverty and death.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.55,0:03:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NTo avoid the negative karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.25,0:04:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He avoid he recommended\Nthat you not reincarnate in the human domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.70,0:04:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And the way you do\Nthat is by uh not having either attractions or aversions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.19,0:04:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And no attractions and no aversions.\NUh uh so for whatever it's worth, we salute the Buddha.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.95,0:04:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And uh however, we're all here.\NI noticed that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.51,0:04:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So I guess we didn't take him too seriously in the\Nprevious lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.87,0:04:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I can hear us singing.\NOh, the boot of that old fogy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.43,0:04:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Who listens to him anyway?\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.91,0:04:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So there we are back in the in the world\Nwhich modern academia uh is now ignoring.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.11,0:04:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And I won't go into my rant\Nand raving about modern academia
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.34,0:04:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,because I've already done that in previous lectures.\NBut uh the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.07,0:05:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that academia has deserted uh the world of uh\Nintellectual integrity of course is why it's now sinking
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.69,0:05:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the in the sinking ship of of relativism.\NWith the exception of community colleges
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.79,0:05:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and places who are still uh calibrated in the mid 400s\Nbut the great universities in the east the great fabled
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.51,0:05:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,names have all shunk below 200.\NCan you believe the greatest insul below 200?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.71,0:05:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's unbelievable.\NI said myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.02,0:05:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh I have permission to ask this.\NThat's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.10,0:05:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NI wish she was lying, but she's not.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.02,0:05:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The great great universities I mean the great fabled\Nnames have been taken over by politically correct super
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.86,0:05:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,supervisors to make sure that they calibrate below 200.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.00,0:05:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's what the pope said\Nthat the fall of western civilization uh is due to two
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.95,0:06:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,things uh on the inroads of Islam\Nwhich have destroyed Europe and uh relativism
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.78,0:06:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,which is destroying uh the United States and academia.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.48,0:06:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,However,\Nso the best place to send your people say
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.75,0:06:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,where should I send my my kids?\NI think in some recent book they gave a list of all the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.88,0:06:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,universities is still calibrated in the 400s\Nand uh community colleges uh calibrated in the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.34,0:06:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nthe safest place to send your your your kid is a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.99,0:06:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,community college and uh if he goes to Yale or Harvard,\Npray.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.79,0:06:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NBecause they have the prestige.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.44,0:06:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why the political left headed for them.\NThey headed for those that have the most prestige.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.75,0:06:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And uh so the community college is where you want to go.\NAnd uh we can personally recommend them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.69,0:07:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we recommend them?\NStand up and recommend them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.43,0:07:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I recommend Community College.\NThen when you go to Cal 440
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.07,0:07:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,when he goes to Calbury's 440 right now Yale\Nand Harvard I think calibrate 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.95,0:07:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So all right.\NSo it's because you've deserted uh the greatest
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.25,0:07:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,accomplishments of uh mankind.\NThe intellectual integrity, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.42,0:07:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,historically goes back to ancient uh someplace rather the\Nancient Greece of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.52,0:07:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Athens and Plato and Aris Aristotle and Socrates.\NUh these are the great uh the great minds of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.02,0:07:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And uh and so you ignore them at your own peril.\NUh because this is integrity
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.50,0:08:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and when you desert integrity,\Nwhat happens is you fall into non-integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.71,0:08:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So evolution is also uh doesn't mean it's progressive uh\Nprogressively positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.43,0:08:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It goes through dips and we see\Nthat mankind recently the consciousness level of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.89,0:08:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,which was up to 207 has dropped down to 204 consciousness\Nlevel of mankind was up to 207 and it's now down to 204.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.73,0:08:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's at 204.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.36,0:08:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NSo, as I said, we were disappointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.37,0:08:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We thought evolution was going to keep going forward\Nand instead it took a downturn.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.90,0:08:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, so that's apparently the nature of evolution.\NIt comes, it fluctuates.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.94,0:08:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not just a smooth ride.\NUh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.82,0:08:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we can't just lay back then and figure that, well,\Nall we have to do is depend on the evolution of
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.21,0:08:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness and we're all going to be fine.\NUh, because that's not so.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.99,0:09:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo, we'll we'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.98,0:09:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,All those are the great names.\NThe difference between um perception
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.93,0:09:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and essence has to do with context and content.\NSo here we have an event.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.31,0:09:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the content in a situation\Nand the perceived event is is uh occurring within the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.53,0:09:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,linear domain.\NThe situation however is nonlinear.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.43,0:09:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So the context is event of event is the context in\Nwhich it happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.48,0:09:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So much argumentation that goes on in politics\Nand economics etc of what's the right move to make.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.23,0:09:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It all depends on the situation.\NSo what a thing is depends not only on content
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.03,0:10:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,but context and the content includes the overall\Nsituation including even the world's situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.71,0:10:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it all right to to check out what's\Nthat security thing right now hung up in Congress?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.37,0:10:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,They can't get it approved anyway.\NThe idea is to protect the lives of Americans.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.55,0:10:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nis it an infringement of human liberty
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.96,0:10:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,or is it a a safeguard of human liberty?\NIt all depends on how you view the context.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.94,0:10:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,How you view the context.\NI myself don't care
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.19,0:10:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,if they listen in on my phone conversations.\NCan't you hear the government pouring all these people
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.26,0:10:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,with these things on banks of them,\Nbuildings of them listening
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.12,0:10:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and and then what did you put in after the mustard?\NDid you fry it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.26,0:10:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You say it's his testicles.\NWe should take him to the doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.44,0:10:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean,\Nrows and rows of Secret Service listening to this with
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.58,0:11:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,earphones.\NThe government's listening to me, baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.75,0:11:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWell, better watch your mouth there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.59,0:11:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I say.\NYou're worried about the government listening to your
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.19,0:11:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,conversation, watch what you say.\NSend the telegram.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.69,0:11:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Go ahead.\NWhat's the next one?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.93,0:11:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the next slide?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.47,0:11:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So we talk about we differentiate the context the overall\Ncontext the spirit the time the age the era uh the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.39,0:11:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,political situation the financial situation before you\Nmake up a decision then the content is just not Newtonian
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.51,0:11:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and measurable at all it depends on the circumstances\Ndepends on the approximate field is the country at war
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.39,0:11:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,or not at war you Just see\Nthat makes all the difference in the world doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.19,0:11:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean you you can't draft people\Nwhen the world is not at war.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.20,0:12:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You hard enough to draft them when it is.\NYou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.35,0:12:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So the overall context is what gives meaning.\NSo there's truth as content depending on context.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.55,0:12:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But then out of content and context you derive meaning.\NSo beyond literal content and the context in
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.31,0:12:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,which it happens is meaning\Nand that is not understood by the public at large.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.71,0:12:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it legal to do that?\NWell, it depends on the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.03,0:12:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But what I want to know is well, so what does that mean?\NWhat does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.87,0:12:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What it means is what's significant.\NNot the event and not the circumstances,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.89,0:12:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,but what's the meaning of that?\NWhat was the Boston Tea Party?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.89,0:12:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the meaning of that?\NThey dumped tea in the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.87,0:12:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that all there was to it?\NNo, that was a protest.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.55,0:13:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a protest.\NTaxation without representation or whatever it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.91,0:13:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Even that's not too interesting.\NSo, what does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.06,0:13:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what does it mean?\NNo taxation without representation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.91,0:13:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?\NWhat does it mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.31,0:13:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So out of all this diffuse jibberjabber\Nand carrying on
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.91,0:13:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and BS the significance then is what is the meaning of it.\NSo what man really wants to know is what is the meaning
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.79,0:13:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,of it?\NAnd the subtrafuge go here's
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.12,0:13:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,where the subtrafuge goes on to avoid acknowledging what\Nis the real meaning of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.15,0:13:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Americans staying alive.\NAmericans staying alive against enemies
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.68,0:13:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that want to destroy you in every way possible\Nand preach hatred of the great white Satan.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.31,0:13:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So what is the meaning of that?\NWhat is the meaning of such legislation?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.67,0:14:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can't go just on content.\NYou can't even go on context while we are at war with
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.25,0:14:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that culture.\NYou have to look to meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.34,0:14:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What are the highest priorities?\NSo there you come into value
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.38,0:14:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and spiritual spiritual significance to keep people free\Nand unencumbered to the degree
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.10,0:14:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that you can allow them freedom uh is what we do for each\Nother as human beings.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.25,0:14:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to see each other survive\Nand prosper as well as we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.15,0:14:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NSo that's goodwill.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.55,0:14:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So the best meaning\Nthat we can attach to a thing is does this serve good
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.79,0:14:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,will?\NAnd I think that one of the best spiritual teachings I
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.67,0:14:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,ever heard was merely people say what can I do to become\Nenlightened and serve the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.71,0:14:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Um come from goodwill and selfless service\Nand unconditional love towards all of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.93,0:15:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Unconditional love towards all of life.\NSo even the person sawing the head off of a missionary
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.66,0:15:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,lady is doing it.\NHow can you have compassion for such cruelty?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.39,0:15:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that person doesn't know any better.\NThey've been indoctrinated indoctrinated.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.31,0:15:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Indoctrinated to think\Nthat what they're doing is serving God.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.91,0:15:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So uh we don't see it that way.\NWe don't see it that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.15,0:15:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But we can understand\Nthat if you were brought up to believe that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.39,0:15:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can see that people get brainwashed into certain\Nactivities and then we can forgive them
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.07,0:15:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,because the meaning is\Nthat they are trying to serve truth
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.56,0:15:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and divinity as they have been taught to serve truth\Nand divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.86,0:15:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So that allows us to be compassionate.\NPeople say how can you be compassionate towards what we
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.08,0:15:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,perceive as evil?\NYou see because they cannot help being the way they are
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.74,0:16:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,at the time they are being that way.\NAnd you know, I practiced psychiatry for 50 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.89,0:16:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And uh many people I saw doing things\Nthat in the rise of the world would be reprehensible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.43,0:16:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And they had no choice in the matter.\NNo choice in the matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.92,0:16:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say, "Why?\N" I said, "I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.62,0:16:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I just blacked out and I did it.\NI just blacked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.10,0:16:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,," Functional hypoglycemia.\NOne of the biggest ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.82,0:16:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,People eat all kinds of sugar.\NTheir blood sugar drops.
