Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.59,1:02:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The idea of a personal self occurs spontaneously.\NSo we don't have to feel guilty that we have it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.48,1:02:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's normal.\NIt's a natural consequence.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.20,1:02:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We see phenomena happen and we presume\Nthat there's a personal self that makes it happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.87,1:02:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We presume that a personal self waves this arm.\NBut if we're fast enough, if we're fast enough,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.50,1:02:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is all a matter of speed,\Nyou will catch that that happened just prior to your
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.70,1:03:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,taking credit for it.\N" Let's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.69,1:03:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That is 110,000 of a second resistance.\NSo the leading edge of the ego then is 110,000 of a
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.21,1:03:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,second ahead of reality.\NAnd you reach a point of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.19,1:03:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,where you can transcend\Nthat onetenth of 110,000 of a second.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.53,1:03:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And you catch that the ego is taking credit for what has\Nalready happened.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.11,1:03:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think I've told you in previous lectures I\Ndiscovered that when I was still an adolescent
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.92,1:03:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,or uh no yeah probably adolescent 18 or 19.\NAnyway,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.72,1:03:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,a rabbit I was driving the car fort and uh\Nand a rabbit ran across the road.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.82,1:03:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Instantly the foot went down on the brake\Nand saved the rabbit
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.54,1:04:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and I caught the ego claiming credit for that.\NI caught the ego saying I put my foot on the brake.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.35,1:04:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The foot was already on the brake\Nwhen the eye jumped in and claim credit for that.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.19,1:04:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So I caught I caught the ego at it at a very young age\Nbefore I knew anything about consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.44,1:04:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,or anything like that.\NEgo jumped in and instantly claimed credit for saving the
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.99,1:04:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,rabbit's life.\NNo, it happened before before the eye made a decision.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.47,1:04:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The instant breaking happened instantly\Nand then the eye complimented itself
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.02,1:04:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,which is egotism which we'll talk about uh later Susan\Nand I if we have time for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.49,1:04:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to just finish the review of these uh particular\Nlectures.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.24,1:04:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo mystical is a word uh
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.87,1:04:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that we will talk there's a few slides on mysticism later.\NMysticism is that emergence as the ego collapses.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.54,1:05:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh the mysticism then is an inner knowingness.\NIt's the inner awareness of the nonlinear.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.99,1:05:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,As the linear as you're less do less\Nand less dominated by the egotism of the linear domain
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.49,1:05:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and thinkingness\Nand you give up thinkingness is a bad habit
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.89,1:05:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and the you let go of thinkingness.\Nawareness takes over.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.54,1:05:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead,\Nthis can be achieved through meditation
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.67,1:05:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh contemplation as well.\NYou can adopt a contemplative style
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.07,1:05:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and way of being aware within the world\Nso that you're not, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.59,1:05:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,not thinking in a linear dimension at all.\NInstead,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.61,1:05:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,you're sort of automatically adjusting to the overall\Nfield in an appropriate way.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.88,1:05:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you're honest with yourself,\Nyou'll see that this is happening of its own.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.14,1:06:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The awareness of consciousness itself is such\Nthat you automatically get out of the way of the trolley
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.00,1:06:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,car.\NUh because that's the sense of reality
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.95,1:06:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that comes out of the infinite field.\NSo the field knows
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.18,1:06:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that you shouldn't be standing on the trolley car tracks\Nand it moves you off.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.95,1:06:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And it isn't that the ego decided, man,\Nit's dangerous standing here.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.12,1:06:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,," You remember ever saying that to yourself?\NI don't think I should be standing on these trolley
Dialogue: 0,1:06:27.88,1:06:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,tracks.\NI think I will get off before the cable car gets here.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.68,1:06:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you do it automatically.\NSo that which we often disregard
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.46,1:06:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,because we say it's just automatic is is the effect of\Nperception.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.09,1:06:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the is is the effect of perception.\NIt's the effect of the knowingness of the infinite field
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.00,1:06:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness itself.\NAs we let go the illusion
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.05,1:06:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that we're being dominated by logic and cause\Nand effect and the linear domain,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.71,1:07:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,we begin to see that we've been taking credit,\Nthat actually everything is happening autonomously by
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.95,1:07:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,itself.\NOnly once in a while does the mind come in uh in any kind
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.08,1:07:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,of a meaningful way.\NYou know,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.54,1:07:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,shall I have a ham sandwich or a cheese sandwich?\NThat was the ego's big moment today.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.19,1:07:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that you are, that you're there,\Nthat you're eating, all this has been decided for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.36,1:07:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that you need to work to make a living\Nand pay the bills, all this,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.98,1:07:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,all this phenomena is outside your your sness.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.22,1:07:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,what you're allowed to choose today is whether you want a\Ncheese sandwich or a ham sandwich.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.29,1:07:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the limit of your freedom.\Nthe idea of free choice.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.60,1:07:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You see,\Nfree choice is one of the great illusions of the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.43,1:07:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And people give up all kinds of stuff for what they call\Nfreedom of speech, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.15,1:07:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And uh anyway, they quickly bring freedom.\NThe way to eliminate freedom of speech is to give people
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.10,1:08:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,real freedom of speech\Nand they will quickly get rid of free speech.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.06,1:08:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,All right?\NThe origination of truth is a spontaneous knowingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.74,1:08:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a radiance.\NIt's like an illumination.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.23,1:08:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, there is no personal self, no cause,\Neffect, no verbs, no me causing of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.95,1:08:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,All right,\Nwe'll go to the next
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.48,1:08:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,because we want to finish all these slides.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.43,1:08:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is always affirmative.\NIt it doesn't say not this, not that.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.46,1:08:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It says this instead of that.\NIt's invitational.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.30,1:08:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not sentimental.\NEmotionality is based on perception.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.80,1:08:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So, a lot of truth gets lost in the emotionality.\NUh this happens in politics very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.44,1:08:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You know,\Nsomething gets to be a popular belief system
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.30,1:08:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and next thing you know, there's a bandwagon.\NEverybody's getting on there.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.47,1:09:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They're waving flags, you know,\Nan earthwarming uh rally or something like this.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.68,1:09:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Except the earth doesn't pay attention to the\Nearthwarming rally.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.30,1:09:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway,\Nso but people get very emotionally committed to causes
Dialogue: 0,1:09:14.14,1:09:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and the narcissistic core of the ego loves to ride the\Nbandwagon on causes.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.96,1:09:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever is a current popular cause,\Nuh how to get rid of your garbage or whatever it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.74,1:09:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,uh people sign up by the drove\Nand become very emotional about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.77,1:09:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So you say why do they have to become emotional about it?\NIt's because the core of the ego is narcissistic.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.47,1:09:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with me me my cause my belief system uh is\Nnow becomes very important.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.74,1:09:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So by exaggerating the importance of a belief system all\Nyou're doing is increasing the magnitude of the egotism.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.66,1:10:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,uh how important your views are on things.\NAs you get more sophisticated,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.87,1:10:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you lose interest in what people's opinions are\Nbecause they're all stupid.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.47,1:10:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And for amusement,\Nyou can click on to the what do you call it?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.03,1:10:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Internet system, gang machine.\NWhat do you call that system anyway?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.53,1:10:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Blo blogger system.\NAnd you can find endless amusement there.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.27,1:10:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,uh from the from the benign to the ridiculous.\NVery ridiculous, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.51,1:10:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh all right.\NSo truth is not sentimental.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.84,1:10:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't uh climb on the bandwagon.\NWe don't have to save the world through enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.70,1:10:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll have a save the world through enlightenment rally\Nin Central Park.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.70,1:10:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,will bring parades and banners and bugles\Nand and important politicians
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.25,1:10:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh save the world through spiritual advancement\Nand consciousness awareness.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:57.91,1:11:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You can imagine how many people will sign up\Nand people who get what we're really about wouldn't be
Dialogue: 0,1:11:10.58,1:11:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,there, would they?\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.41,1:11:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's truth does not do anything or cause anything.\NIt's nonvolitional.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:20.70,1:11:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's invitational.\NPeople are either attracted to it
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.61,1:11:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's meaningful to them or not.\NIt's nonpredictive.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:29.38,1:11:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't predict the future.\NSo the prediction of what's going to happen 2020
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.18,1:11:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,something rather >> 12 >> 2012 >> December >> get your\Nmortgage paid up by December.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.22,1:11:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Right before Christmas, right?\NOh golly.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.27,1:11:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,God doesn't even care about Christmas.\NHe's going to put bring the world to an end right before
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.64,1:11:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Christmas.\NOh, that's not very kindly.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.92,1:12:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I'll have to speak to him upstairs.\NYou could wait till after Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.11,1:12:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,have the world in December 26, 2012.\NSee, Because it's based on an idea of causality.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.43,1:12:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,See, because the world is evolutionary.\NWhat's going to be next cannot be decided now
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.19,1:12:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,because what happens is the phenomena of the future are\Nthe result of decision joint decisions made now.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.43,1:12:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way of knowing what will happen\Nbecause nobody knows what choices
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.18,1:12:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,because of freedom of choice\Nbecause of freedom of the will.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.77,1:12:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's impossible to predict the future of anything\Nbecause otherwise you there would be no freedom of the
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.16,1:12:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,will.\NIf there was no freedom of the will,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.75,1:12:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,there would be no answerability.\NThere'd be no such thing as karma etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.13,1:13:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither would there be liberation.\NSo the future cannot be predicted
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.16,1:13:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,because the future is the consequence of the present\Nand the present hasn't happened yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.43,1:13:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What will be in the future depends on all the choices\Nthat people make
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.73,1:13:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and those seeing this as of right now those are\Nunknowable.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.51,1:13:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way of knowing\Nwhich way the wind will be blowing on that day
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.71,1:13:25.49,Default,,0,0,0,,because the factors\Nthat contribute to the direction of the wind haven't
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.49,1:13:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,occurred yet.\NIs that obvious?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.72,1:13:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody got any problem about that?\NNobody.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.23,1:13:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh well.\NIt reminds me that was
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.44,1:13:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that old joke about the kid in the back said the world's\Ngoing to end in in 20 20 billion years.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.27,1:13:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The guy who puts his hand up 20 billion years.\NYes, that's Oh my god, I thought you said 20 million.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.55,1:13:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nthe reason I can safely predict
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.25,1:14:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that the world is not coming to to an end in the year\N2012 because if it is,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.00,1:14:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,nobody would be around to tell me I'm wrong.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.04,1:14:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm betting that the world will still be here in the year\N2012, December 21st or whatever it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.28,1:14:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And besides,\NGod wouldn't be that much of a killjoy
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.92,1:14:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and knock Christmas out.\NI don't you wait till December 27th anyway after you open
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.87,1:14:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,your stockings and all that kind of stuff.\NI mean, that would be mean, wouldn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:37.43,1:14:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nit's not predictive and it's not predictive
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.73,1:14:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the freedom of the will.\NKarmic responsibility is
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.81,1:14:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,because you have the freedom of choice.\NFreedom of choice is what differentiates the
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.47,1:14:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness level of humans.\NHuh?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.21,1:14:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of freedom of choice\Nthat you can reach salvation.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.36,1:15:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Salvation is be is a consequence of one's own personal\Nchoice.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.34,1:15:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So God doesn't force anybody to do anything.\NEach one of us by virtue of the choices and decisions
Dialogue: 0,1:15:10.00,1:15:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that we make from moment to moment uh decide our own\Nkarmic future and propensities.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.08,1:15:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So I always compare the infinite field of conscious\Nconsciousness uh to a giant electromagnetic field
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.11,1:15:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and I compare human beings uh our little spirits to\Nlittle fragments of metal fragments
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.76,1:15:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and we have a positive and a negative pole.\NSo as we make positive choices our polarity moves in this
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.93,1:15:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,direction and as we make negative choices our polarity\Nmoves in this direction.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.65,1:15:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So based on the choices you make then like a little iron\Nmagnetic filing your position in the infinite magnetic
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.11,1:15:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,field shifts.\NSo if you constantly choose the negative you shift down
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.84,1:16:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,towards this level of the field closer\Nand closer to the hells
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.00,1:16:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and as you choose on this side the other polarity comes\Nup and because of the infinite power of the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.51,1:16:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So therefore God is not personal\Nand judgmental God is the infinite field of power out of
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.06,1:16:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,which your choices are what decide your your fate.\Nyour your fate.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.17,1:16:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Your choices are you know your fate is strictly up to\Nyour own choices.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.55,1:16:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Your fate is not up to an arbitrary god\Nbut strictly within your own hands.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.39,1:16:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NStrictly within your own power.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.66,1:16:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NYour karmic destiny is strictly within your own personal
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.77,1:16:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,power.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.83,1:16:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.\NSo there's no point of uh fearing a god who would act in
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.26,1:16:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,contrary to his own laws.\NSo the law of divinity is an infinite field of infinite
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.56,1:17:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,power within that infinite field of infinite power.\NYour choices decide your own fate.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.14,1:17:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So everyone lives then by the ultimate freedom of his own\Nchoices which by virtue of the infinite power of the
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.03,1:17:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,field of divinity determines the outcomes.\NWe say that God is omnisient, all- knowing, omnipotent,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.64,1:17:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,all powerful, allpresent, all knowing, all powerful.\NBecause of the nature of the field,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.81,1:17:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,then our karmic destiny is within our own hand.\NThere is nobody else steering the canoe except ourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.14,1:17:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,\NGod neither needs to be feared nor hated nor held
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.67,1:17:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,responsible.\NAnd we alone are responsible for our own destiny.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.63,1:17:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We alone are responsible for our own karmic destiny.\NAnd is by virtue of that that we reach freedom
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.30,1:18:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and eventually resist otherwise.\NIf you weren't responsible,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.50,1:18:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you'd never be able to reach freedom either.\NSo all right.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.23,1:18:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So becoming enlightened then is just progressively seeing\Nall the things that we're talking about until they become
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.71,1:18:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,automatic.\NUh so we said that one quality of spiritual truth is it's
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.25,1:18:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,not p not predictive\Nbecause there's no possible way of knowing the future
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.29,1:18:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,if the future depends on the choices\Nthat are being made currently by everyone on earth.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.35,1:18:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,All right?\NIt's non authoritarian.
